## 1. Project Concept

**Algorithmic Gallery** is an interactive gallery experience where sculptures bloom when gazed at and decay when ignored. A recommendation engine tracks user preferences across three emotional phases, critiquing algorithmic attention retention (like TikTok's For You page).

The visitor walks through procedurally-arranged gallery rooms. Sculptures start greyscale and small (seeds). When the visitor gazes at one, it blooms — saturating with color, growing, emitting light. When they look away, it decays — desaturating, dissolving, shrinking. Behind the scenes, a recommendation engine learns what the visitor lingers on and curates increasingly manipulative selections, mirroring how platforms like TikTok engineer engagement.

**Three emotional phases:**
1. **Fascination** — broad exploration, showing diverse objects (70% explore / 30% exploit)
2. **Recognition** — the visitor notices patterns in what's shown; engine exploits preferences with strategic adjacent probing (30% explore / 70% exploit)
3. **Unease** — aggressive exploitation of top preferences with wild-swing "Hail Mary" explores from lowest-scoring tags (15% explore / 85% exploit), creating an uncanny feeling of being watched/known

**Platform:** Desktop-first (keyboard/mouse FPS controls), VR as optional enhancement (Quest 3, head gaze). Everything runs locally — no server, no internet. Must be packageable as a standalone game.

**Asset source:** ~14,000 models from the [Source Engine Blender Collection](https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3170975582) (Portal, Portal 2, Half-Life 2, Team Fortress 2). These are .blend files with Source Engine custom materials (VertexLitGeneric node groups), batch-exported to .glb for Unity runtime loading.

